    "recap_headline": "Baseball",
    "recap_text": "LOS ANGELES\n\u2013 The No. 13 USC baseball team took down Washington 14-4 in a seven-inning, run-rule victory on Sunday afternoon at Dedeaux Field, finishing off a three-game sweep of the Huskies.\nIt was USC's fourth run-rule victory as the Trojans move to 24-1 overall and 8-1 in Big Ten play. Washington falls to 9-14, 4-5.\u00a0The Trojans' 24-1 record is the best in program history through 25 games.\nUSC quickly erased a 1-0 deficit in the first, scoring five runs on four hits in the opening frame.\nBrock Slaton\ncapped the five-run inning with a two-run double as part of his four-RBI day.\nUSC would put up runs in six of the seven innings on Sunday as the offense kept the pressure on all game. Slaton later hit a two-run homer in the third and then\nAndrew Lamb\nhit a three-run shot in the sixth to make it a 13-4 ballgame.\nAugie Lopez's\nsingle up the middle in the seventh scored\nMaddox Riske\n, pushing it to a 10-run lead and ending the game.\nThe Trojans scored their 14 runs on 11 hits, with eight players recording hits and RBI in the contest.\nAndrew Johnson\ngave up three runs in his 4.0 innings of work on the mound, with\nHenry Chabot\ngiving up one run in 2.0 innings and\nSax Matson\ntossing a scoreless top of the seventh.\nTOP PERFORMERS\nBrock Slaton\n: 2-for-4, 4 RBI, 2-R HR, 2B\nAndrew Lamb\n: 1-for-3, 3 RBI, 2R, 3-R HR\nDean Carpentier\n: 1-for-2, RBI, 3R, 2BB\nHenry Chabot\n: W, 2.0 IP, H, R, BB, 3K\nCOMING UP\nUSC hosts No. 17 Oregon State on Tuesday before heading to Maryland for a three-game series starting on Friday. All four games this week will be broadcast on B1G+.\nHear from\n@BrockSlaton\nafter he drove in 4 runs in his first start of the season \u270c\ufe0f\n#FightOn\nx\n@YETICoolers\npic.twitter.com/Fhy6fvRNIv\n\u2014 USC Baseball (@USC_Baseball)\nMarch 22, 2026",
